<div class='talk-speaker media'>
<a class='talk-speaker__image media__image media__image--thumb' href='/speakers/severine_autesserre'>
<span class="thumb thumb--square"><span class="thumb__sizer"><span class="thumb__tugger"><img alt="" class=" thumb__image" play="false" src="https://tedcdnpi-a.akamaihd.net/r/tedcdnpe-a.akamaihd.net/images/ted/3a4088303bbc413cdb18d7497ec04ae7ef8a0699_254x191.jpg?" /><span class="thumb__aligner"></span></span></span></span>
</a>
<div class='talk-speaker__details media__message'>
<div class='talk-speaker__name h10'>
<a class="l3 talk-speaker__link" href="/speakers/severine_autesserre">Severine Autesserre</a>
</div>
<div class='talk-speaker__description'>
Peace and conflict researcher
</div>
<div class='talk-speaker__bio'>
Severine Autesserre traces civil war and endemic violence to its roots, and its resolution, in local and interpersonal conflicts.
<a class="l3 talk-speaker__link" href="/speakers/severine_autesserre">Full bio</a>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

